key.name: Young soldier

key.name: Soldier
key.description: The Soldier is the foundation of any army. Its body is a weapon of war.

key.name: Doorkeeper
key.description: The Doorkeeper's big head is able to seal off the passage to the nest. They are great defenders, but their atrophied legs make them useless at offense.

key.name: Top doorkeeper

key.name: Fire ant
key.description: Fire Ants can spray formic acid amongst opponents, causing them to melt. Their attacks are usually lethal. They attack from behind the front line for safety.

key.name: Top fire ant
key.description: The elite of the Fire Ants. They blow anything that moves to pieces.

key.name: Top soldier
key.description: The elite of the Soldiers. They are sturdy, fast, and lethal.

key.name: Tank
key.description: Tanks are as original a concept as they are devastating. It is actually one giant ant supported by 4 smaller ants. They charge into the enemy ranks causing extensive damage. However, they are utterly ineffective to defend.

key.name: Top tank
key.description: Legend tells that after many fights, the most powerful tanks can enter to the elite. These exceptional ants no more fight, they massacre...

key.name: Killer
key.description: These ants are equipped with a poisoned dart. A target hit is a target dead.
